 ENUGU State Governor Ifeanyi Ugwuanyi has directed civil servants to resume work on Monday, August 3. The directive was contained in a statement by the Secretary to the State Government, Prof. Simon Uchenna Ortuanya. The state government advised returning civil servants to observe Nigeria Centre for Disease Control (NCDC) protocols for the containment of the spread of Coronavirus Disease (COVID-19), “including handwashing with soap, use of alcohol-based hand sanitizer, compulsory use of face shield/mask and maintaining social distancing”.